<clause id="_89996655-a82f-e883-475e-2a6eaeb324ab" obligation="normative">
<title id="_7b8cf25f-0c24-28b8-2d70-779b6ec7af78">Emission Event Class</title>
<p id="_eaeab25c-a3db-5fc2-5b2c-8b3272d68477">An Emission Event is an occurrent representing the release of a substance into the atmosphere over a non-zero duration. It is characterized by its start time and end time, the Source Feature from which the substance originated, and the identity and quantity of the emitted substance.</p>

<table id="_dd752797-7326-1898-b5d0-2e044a2879b8" width="90%"><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr id="_70cb2494-9112-51d8-568f-c09646923558"><td id="_f817e055-afa6-8403-85ae-bcfda67c1ce1" valign="middle" align="left"><strong>Requirement 1: Emission Event Class</strong> </td>
<td id="_1e5e9a8c-2d23-08a4-2ee5-d2374c0e68ca" valign="middle" align="left">/req/datamodel/core/emission-event<br/> <br/>  Each Emission Event class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in  <xref target="emission-event-attributes"/>. Each Emission Event class shall have the direct relation between an Emission Event class and other classes listed in  <xref target="emission-event-relations"/>.</td>
</tr></tbody>
</table>

<table id="_6e9c2b9b-44d8-b97a-0cd1-ebbc2a34991d" anchor="emission-event-attributes" width="90%">
<name id="_42105269-5fb4-4b8c-0c7c-cde13da87486">Attributes of an Emission Event class</name>
