<clause id="_06b5daaf-2ebd-ca3b-ddef-22bf7802476d" obligation="normative">
<title id="_eb406fe5-9388-1def-2899-6d08338fdf86">Observation Class</title>
<p id="_c1f67996-b531-cc67-1aac-f018e156a5a6">An Observation is evidence that may support an Emission Quantity or Temporal Bound assertion. An Observation has a result, a time, and an ultimate feature of interest (the Source to which the observation ultimately pertains).</p>

<table id="_d359ec6c-1708-e57e-4602-3e49c9b89196" width="“90%”"><tbody><tr id="_c3035511-c435-c7c9-92c8-026df2ff044c"><td id="_670703be-94bf-6bac-843b-e3e5a4205994" valign="middle" align="left">Requirement 5: Observation Class </td>
<td id="_997ea655-d5f9-ce3f-933f-d9d91990375f" valign="middle" align="left">/req/datamodel/core/observation<br/> + Each Observation class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in &lt;&gt;. Each Observation class shall have the direct relation between an Observation class and other classes listed in &lt;&gt;.</td>
</tr></tbody>
</table>

<table id="_3f7969ca-bab3-18fc-219d-f80d23523ad3" anchor="observation-attributes" width="“90%”">
<name id="_6b659ff2-9443-05e4-bc65-e7934def4af0">Attributes of an Observation class</name>
<tbody><tr id="_d881363a-e1d7-a47a-cd48-f22a63461edb"><td id="_c6291b27-712e-c1a9-0241-59a9349e3e11" valign="middle" align="left">Names</td>
<td id="_f7518a02-3090-73d7-82ac-696506f3dd2d" valign="middle" align="left">Definition</td>
<td id="_037e4524-1b1d-8f6a-be2b-14351523b78f" valign="middle" align="left">Data types and values</td>
<td id="_a99546e4-2908-5c9e-5fb2-f44a00a01a52" valign="middle" align="left">Multiplicity and use</td>
</tr><tr id="_bbb9f1cd-3661-b910-5236-0f9e074d2a31"><td id="_6bb91cad-f353-4a7d-b640-76ec446fe790" valign="middle" align="left">result</td>
<td id="_9711f0ba-8f95-566c-9bc9-4a8d90da7603" valign="middle" align="left">The result value of the observation.</td>
<td id="_fc0a35fa-0cf5-9c23-7f97-c7fadbdba460" valign="middle" align="left">any</td>
<td id="_da73a223-b55d-f2b7-8da1-81839e461140" valign="middle" align="left">1 (mandatory)</td>
</tr><tr id="_a98d9b16-e0fb-6df3-2390-6c6cb0a13f77"><td id="_1d70bb92-ef7d-1b8a-a88e-f51116e73714" valign="middle" align="left">time</td>
<td id="_6e49596f-9e0c-9da4-9781-ab24f0c2aaec" valign="middle" align="left">The time instant at which the observation result applies.</td>
<td id="_cc33bc4d-6a75-e8f0-d769-6fc305541a49" valign="middle" align="left">TM_Instant</td>
<td id="_6d00e45c-77d3-f3f3-8b1d-9f9612755c38" valign="middle" align="left">1 (mandatory)</td>
</tr></tbody>
</table>

<table id="_b9c63b81-b837-4f15-b68a-a062287a8ca6" anchor="observation-relations" width="“90%”">
<name id="_8c11daed-5135-eade-f423-5c5fd9dd4bbc">Direct relation between an Observation class and other class types</name>
<tbody><tr id="_2bfc689a-bb04-3743-4ef5-78c27a72e4b6"><td id="_14fb624c-30eb-aaba-ef63-a008a288c329" valign="middle" align="left">Role</td>
<td id="_3e8c15a2-60de-dbfc-dced-b293cebe7403" valign="middle" align="left">Description</td>
<td id="_18cd7f94-af31-ae7c-761a-bfea3b935408" valign="middle" align="left">Target Class Type</td>
<td id="_1398d694-5af9-180e-0ec6-8f4330a55532" valign="middle" align="left">Multiplicity and use</td>
</tr><tr id="_df8155e3-0555-e824-03db-97c43b666179"><td id="_e0e29372-6cab-d52b-1e40-f756dcee3413" valign="middle" align="left">ultimateFeatureOfInterest</td>
<td id="_189dc282-f074-22eb-8e04-fa266aabe7e4" valign="middle" align="left">The Source that is the ultimate feature of interest of the observation.</td>
<td id="_c4b720e1-4e0f-21ff-2047-69805b8eaa19" valign="middle" align="left">Source</td>
<td id="_cc95056e-bbb3-cb73-0ecb-88b5d4da6a27" valign="middle" align="left">1 (mandatory)</td>
</tr></tbody>
</table>
</clause>

<clause id="_9755a36a-6050-3a9d-c7cb-e82cb7894216" obligation="normative">
<title id="_1e31d618-ee25-c7dd-90f6-d994dbfdc7cc">Temporal Bound Class</title>
<p id="_6c7f9153-48ec-9fd0-9c1f-69ac013361cc">A Temporal Bound is a value object representing a temporal assertion (e.g., start time or end time) with optional data quality metadata. Temporal bounds may be supported by evidence observations and are associated with a determination method.</p>

<table id="_71220e54-29ac-774d-2439-043885c71b89" width="“90%”"><tbody><tr id="_845d27ad-e6f0-4d36-8866-1b439f95803a"><td id="_09ae1e25-cdde-ce55-2763-c7bd462cde3e" valign="middle" align="left">Requirement 4: Temporal Bound Class </td>
<td id="_b0adad60-29df-d8e2-b1fe-a6795b58bea8" valign="middle" align="left">/req/datamodel/core/temporal-bound<br/> + Each Temporal Bound class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in &lt;&gt;. Each Temporal Bound class shall have the direct relation between a Temporal Bound class and other classes listed in &lt;&gt;.</td>
</tr></tbody>
</table>

<table id="_1c7cdf34-ecb9-8373-d3b1-e4c31ced0bac" anchor="temporal-bound-attributes" width="“90%”">
<name id="_29c29464-1f7e-84ee-611c-5991da91ca16">Attributes of a Temporal Bound class</name>
<tbody><tr id="_acd2642f-e17f-549a-f1de-99cc0240ed87"><td id="_62ed81c1-62a8-b4a5-2db0-1cee56b519ef" valign="middle" align="left">Names</td>
<td id="_952a48b0-6b3e-8237-78e9-68b0cdb02569" valign="middle" align="left">Definition</td>
<td id="_72993894-cd98-23fe-0278-fc6d97c83f7c" valign="middle" align="left">Data types and values</td>
<td id="_4520f1af-e15e-3bf0-b785-f1cd6b3dd7ec" valign="middle" align="left">Multiplicity and use</td>
</tr><tr id="_87be8b8d-75e8-541f-0d91-6d6327b2f886"><td id="_6e1d09c6-2008-9e06-0969-4bc649f8c3ac" valign="middle" align="left">time</td>
<td id="_dc017fe3-c04e-2bb1-f0d6-9da87b078589" valign="middle" align="left">The time instant asserted by this temporal bound.</td>
<td id="_686673b2-5dcd-f37a-0d68-58f2779e191d" valign="middle" align="left">TM_Instant</td>
<td id="_c4b25b33-7587-16bf-2d53-07e3fc29a1cd" valign="middle" align="left">1 (mandatory)</td>
</tr><tr id="_0eceb4cf-65ac-a6ec-4fbb-045108ddb492"><td id="_84bc4699-2d26-cecf-a0a1-19f4c92cc034" valign="middle" align="left">quality</td>
<td id="_ace3ee2c-9b2f-8f85-7ce1-2854040ee9f0" valign="middle" align="left">A data quality element describing the quality of the temporal bound.</td>
<td id="_70ee8f76-441a-cc2d-83a8-420acc661ce4" valign="middle" align="left">DQ_Element</td>
<td id="_b3451df4-06ec-2243-571e-75feb0bb36e8" valign="middle" align="left">0..1 (optional)</td>
</tr></tbody>
</table>

<table id="_9531dd3c-1d4a-d39e-bfb1-db0b90e6f387" anchor="temporal-bound-relations" width="“90%”">
<name id="_d9682ea4-48a9-bbad-3517-17bcf67961f1">Direct relation between a Temporal Bound class and other class types</name>
<tbody><tr id="_8c44ea63-3d5f-1819-e91a-38da85fb5b43"><td id="_d2d2c8ae-dc60-aaa5-c147-9f67c2c95c63" valign="middle" align="left">Role</td>
<td id="_786a6834-84fd-af84-c95b-c4b40b23f2d0" valign="middle" align="left">Description</td>
<td id="_6beb844b-3c46-9a7e-4d72-aa32d89192ad" valign="middle" align="left">Target Class Type</td>
<td id="_7a3ea0a4-99a7-32e1-30fd-6c236a263a3f" valign="middle" align="left">Multiplicity and use</td>
</tr><tr id="_b93969c9-3617-fb44-ee5e-781539dbe65f"><td id="_939c5c80-7559-895f-500a-713e688e7876" valign="middle" align="left">hasDeterminationMethod</td>
<td id="_42102ac4-a038-eb1f-d6a5-f01c504e22ce" valign="middle" align="left">The method used to determine or derive the temporal bound.</td>
<td id="_56eb8c3b-c22e-936e-6854-fc86ae8c0c80" valign="middle" align="left">DeterminationMethod</td>
<td id="_8dcac633-0db7-0548-aa24-ce338bebc6c0" valign="middle" align="left">1 (mandatory)</td>
</tr><tr id="_014b8cdb-60fd-7305-dea6-0f4c188f04ab"><td id="_d2c63bcf-0cec-666c-be37-1b597f72c332" valign="middle" align="left">hasEvidence</td>
<td id="_9bfcce01-82df-2a56-b160-6ab1677bef8f" valign="middle" align="left">Observations that provide evidence supporting the temporal bound assertion.</td>
<td id="_7eb06c2d-89d9-3ef8-4386-eec395a2b28e" valign="middle" align="left">Observation</td>
<td id="_24099e91-a349-ff5e-e596-874e3a56d1bd" valign="middle" align="left">0..* (optional)</td>
</tr></tbody>
</table>
</clause>

<clause id="_1c076f62-e401-eb8f-546a-f34509734dbf" obligation="normative">
<title id="_3313a11b-a9fb-1e72-f7fd-289bec49a298">Unit of Measure Class</title>
<p id="_fe800c77-7c1b-f4d4-ffab-33194d705748">A Unit of Measure provides the unit metadata for an Emission Quantity, including a human-readable name, a symbol, and a URI that links to an external unit definition.</p>

<table id="_b4a1faca-eced-680b-1f66-d0692cc81077" width="“90%”"><tbody><tr id="_e4d55aa4-1465-9b19-8098-887313cc616c"><td id="_690f78da-f53d-19a1-7695-7f96fd92617b" valign="middle" align="left">Requirement 3: Unit of Measure Class </td>
<td id="_dae32041-885f-fdbb-de05-b9405813e891" valign="middle" align="left">/req/datamodel/core/unit-of-measure<br/> + Each Unit of Measure class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in &lt;&gt;. Each Unit of Measure class shall have the direct relation between a Unit of Measure class and other classes listed in &lt;&gt;.</td>
</tr></tbody>
</table>

<table id="_e3fc8629-64ce-1a55-ec17-3abaf492dd94" anchor="unit-of-measure-attributes" width="“90%”">
<name id="_cdef43ce-32a8-2f62-6a86-6a1cc0eb63cb">Attributes of a Unit of Measure class</name>
<tbody><tr id="_4764b590-84ea-6ddc-178f-53bb5eb0a216"><td id="_e836cd88-9942-0f5c-dc01-e8751e4a99b1" valign="middle" align="left">Names</td>
<td id="_12fdb666-a6d9-4af6-4c5f-86436bb91d98" valign="middle" align="left">Definition</td>
<td id="_d6862568-b82c-65f4-183c-0416038a1ad2" valign="middle" align="left">Data types and values</td>
<td id="_96680044-5089-0fc2-ea44-ad493a54a285" valign="middle" align="left">Multiplicity and use</td>
</tr><tr id="_c2263e45-956c-c673-da76-18f26a010878"><td id="_86f2a441-c074-f7b8-9ede-c2a534a60b5a" valign="middle" align="left">name</td>
<td id="_b7a72767-44fb-31db-04e0-28349e40a8ca" valign="middle" align="left">A human-readable name for the unit of measure.</td>
<td id="_2958d9bb-0f37-2283-c5b7-16629a16ff27" valign="middle" align="left">String</td>
<td id="_513d4423-2a46-3a0c-3217-28e3187d8f70" valign="middle" align="left">1 (mandatory)</td>
</tr><tr id="_5cc873b5-fc9d-3bc4-6e38-2229ced2935b"><td id="_345dfeea-4293-cd75-3ac0-c0625c4ad233" valign="middle" align="left">symbol</td>
<td id="_cf5228e3-7eeb-4edb-9b15-fd79b03f5f71" valign="middle" align="left">A short symbol representing the unit of measure.</td>
<td id="_42d3810a-1a22-c6df-e2ca-2dd24ae288c2" valign="middle" align="left">String</td>
<td id="_04a56755-e904-2589-358e-cbf8cb818f23" valign="middle" align="left">1 (mandatory)</td>
</tr><tr id="_5cecaad0-d00e-6e54-6ca1-e68c24ca20e2"><td id="_2e001ff5-7b8e-2e5d-1e2f-ea9709451c98" valign="middle" align="left">definition</td>
<td id="_4d933190-1f6e-9414-6094-ecd0c267c6e2" valign="middle" align="left">The URI linking to an external definition of the unit of measure.</td>
<td id="_ed5fa5fa-11eb-3ee4-9369-bf7b9a586128" valign="middle" align="left">URI</td>
<td id="_8b177996-0ce6-a30c-d321-bec02b6c8606" valign="middle" align="left">1 (mandatory)</td>
</tr></tbody>
</table>

<table id="_734e752f-0ee7-0cd8-5f09-85a7f918fdec" anchor="unit-of-measure-relations" width="“90%”">
